                                     },
                       "message":  "MENU-SHORTCUT-DISPLAY: show File/Edit accelerators next to menu items\n\nDisplay-only menu-deepening beat after #302/#303. File and Edit menu items now\nrender their real keyboard accelerator (Ctrl+O / Ctrl+S / Ctrl+Shift+S / Ctrl+Z\n/ Ctrl+Y) as egui right-aligned shortcut_text, sourced from the existing\neditor-ui Shortcut substrate carried on MenuEntry.shortcut. No command-execution\nchange, no new crate edge, no keystroke-routing change — clicking still\ndispatches; the accelerator is a passive hint.\n\n- build_main_menu_entries attaches .with_shortcut(..) to the 3 File + 2 Edit\n  entries; the projection widens from (label, Command) to\n  (label, Option\u003caccelerator-display\u003e, Command), sourced straight from each\n  resolved MenuEntry.shortcut via Shortcut::display. Play/View project None.\n- render: a small menu_item helper builds each Button + optional shortcut_text;\n  the four menu loops call it (Play still passes its per-item PIE enablement).\n- menu_tests: the four equality tests now pin the accelerator strings AND\n  Play/View=None (the deferral); the round-trip destructures widened; one\n  focused test asserts the File/Edit display strings + the Play/View deferral.\n\nScope decision — File/Edit only: they mirror the live, executing editor-shell\nkeystroke routing (EditorKeyCommand + the Ctrl+O arm). Play\u0027s only shortcut data\nis the toolbar\u0027s advisory F5/Esc hints, which don\u0027t match the real Space/Escape\nPIE binds; surfacing them would open the advisory-vs-real accelerator/execution\nconflict this display-only dispatch avoids. View\u0027s Reset Camera has no binding.\n\nThe File/Edit additions pushed editor-egui-host/lib.rs back over the §1.3 Rule-3\n1000-line cap (which #301 had cleared via test extraction); re-added the\nsplit-cap exemption annotation and deferred the menu-module extraction to a\ndedicated follow-up (EGUIHOST-MENU-EXTRACTION), and corrected the now-stale\nmenu_tests.rs cap claim.\n\nGate: VERIFY OK 7/7 + 10/10 arch lints; cargo check/test/fmt clean.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
